<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by Belinar on 04-26-2001 06:10 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I (for one) have roleplayed (lvl 15 Crazymage in AD&D right now. LOL -Personal creation with me and our gaming group-) I agree with pretty much all of the rp'ing stuff said out there...but it is a game. If you truely want a good RP experience, play table top. I'm not saying to go and cheat either...but you have to expect things like that. 

--Don't tell me that you've never come up with a better solution to a problem than your DM and he said "OK...we'll do it your way" or at the very least "Roll a dex check and see if you pull it off". Pathing buggs are just that. You found out something a more helpfull sollution to the problem than the  'original GM's' (Verant Programmers) had in mind, and your ability to exploit it means 'You won the Dex roll...good for you'--

Understand that I don't encourage it, but come'on. Why yell at some ppl just because they can stand behind some kill holes and attack an oncomming army with arrows without being placed in "much" danger....Oh way, that happened in RL...nm

That's my point...the person is in danger...if you move 1 inch to the right, you get attacked...if you move 1/2 inch to the left, you get attacked...in either case, you die. If you're good enough to get to the "bugged spot" and survive, you deserve at least a little exp for it, if not all you can suck out of the Brainless mobs.

I for one don't use pathing buggs. 
--Mainly because I don't know about many, and I get powerleveled when I need it...key word there...NEED!!!--

I say do what you like, but understand that there will be ppl out there that will yell at you for doing something "THEY DEAM AS CHEATING" and thus report you. unfortunately Verant GM's agree with them, and will probibly take steps to stop you. 
--Why they don't take steps to stop powerlevelers too, I can't say, but they don't--

You can cheat if you want to...just leave me alone and we'll all be happy.

..."Live to play, or get out of the way!!!"...
</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
